sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
It is a transcriptional unit including 37℃ induced RBS + tetR + double terminator.
It can be added various promoter to adapt your conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: KUO, CHIA-CHUN
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: the 37℃ induced RBS cames from iGEM08_TUDelft
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
To regulate following genes by temperature.
To maintain cells at 37?? C ↑ : the tetR protein be generated and repress Ptet's circuit.
To release cells at 37?? C ↓ : the tetR protein not be generated and do not repress Ptet's circuit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539711
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region of ilvC from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr(MG1655). It encodes ketol-acid reductoisomerase NAD(P)-binding which is part of the isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because of the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding gene, we have to delete those RE site in kivd. The RE site in the part has been modified by point mutation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

Lutz R, Bujard H., Independent and tight regulation of transcriptional units in Escherichia coli via the LacR/O, the TetR/O and AraC/I1-I2 regulatory elements. Nucleic Acids Res. 1997 Mar 15;25(6):1203-10. PMID: 9092630

References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

Lutz R, Bujard H., Independent and tight regulation of transcriptional units in Escherichia coli via the LacR/O, the TetR/O and AraC/I1-I2 regulatory elements. Nucleic Acids Res. 1997 Mar 15;25(6):1203-10. PMID: 9092630

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
